text:
The band formed in 1987 in Burriana (Castellón). Their first lineup was Pedro, Viçent, Oscar, Natxo y Manolo. However, before recording their first album, Feo replaced  Natxo. In 1991 they released their first LP, "No soporto vuestras caras." In 1992 "Soldadito Español" came out, and finally in 1993 "Que se repartan el mundo."
The formation changed again with the exit of Manolo and the arrival of Nano before their fourth disc, "Esperando al viento" in 1995. After "A cara de perro," out in 1998, "Senderos de este infierno," their first Live Disc, came out in 1999, followed by their seventh album, "Bulla" in 2000.
In 2002, the band released "Veneno", with the exit of Viçent and the arrival of Tonet. In 2003, the band released "Ay, de mi!" and "Insurgente" in 2005.
In 2006, the band released their second live album and first compilation named "¡Vivos... por domesticar!".
"Quemaste tus alas de angel" was released in 2007 leading to a tour, during which Nano and Tonet left the band, replaced by Kusio and Sam. At that time only Pedro and Oscar remained from the original members.
In 2009 EUKZ released their newest material, named "La burbuja".
El Último Ke Zierre also known as EUKZ is a punk band from Borriana, Spain formed in 1987.
